# TYPO3 13 conformance

- Target TYPO3 13.4 LTS only. Do not introduce TYPO3 14 requirements.
- Prefer TYPO3 core APIs, DI, PSR-14 events, static TCA, and typed PHP 8.2 code.
- Keep the extension layout coherent across `Classes/`, `Configuration/`, `Documentation/`, and `Tests/`.
- Favor `declare(strict_types=1);`, explicit parameter/return types, and `final` on non-extension classes.
- Remove legacy globals and runtime patterns when a TYPO3 13 API exists.
- Treat missing tests, missing CI, stale docs, and weak composer metadata as conformance gaps.

## Report loop

- Write findings to `Build/Reports/typo3-conformance-report.md`.
- Separate findings from fixes. Commit the report first, then commit remediation work.
- Focus on high-value gaps that also unblock TYPO3 13 compatibility.
